{title: Emily}
{artist: Joanna Newsom}
{meta: type Chords}

Standard tuning, capo on 3. This will make things a little easier for you.
If you're new to guitar, sorry, you're still gonna have to use bar chords (but shout out to you
for trying to take on a 12 minute song).

Chords used (relative to capo)
[C]      x32010
[Em]     022000
[D]      xx0232
[Am]     x02210
[F]      133211
[A]      x02220
[E]      022100
[F#m]    244222
[Amaj7]  x02120
[Bm]     224432
[C#m]    446654
[F#]     244322
[G#m]    466444
[B]      224442

Quite a few! but less bar chords than you'd have to use in another tab, so it should be
a little nicer to your hands.


{comment: Verse 1}
[C]The m[Em]eadowlark and the ch[D]im-choo-ree and the s[Am]parrow
[C]S[Em]et to the sky in a fl[D]ying spree, for the s[Am]port of the Pharaoh
[C]L[Em]ittle while later the Ph[D]arisees dragged a c[Am]omb through the meadow
[C]D[Em]o you remember what they ca[D]lled up to you and m[Am]e, in our window?
[C]There is a r[Em]usty light on the pi[D]nes tonight, sun pouring w[Am]ine, lord, or marrow
[C]Into the b[Em]ones of the birches and the sp[D]ires of the churches juttin' o[Am]ut from the shadow
[C]and the y[Em]oke and the axe, and the ol[D]d smokestacks, and the b[Am]ale and the barrow
[C]and e[Em]verything sloped like it was dr[D]agged from the rope in the m[Am]outh of the south below

{comment: Verse 2}
[F]W[A]e've seen those m[E]ountains kneeling, f[F#m]elten and grey
[F]W[A]e thought our v[E]ery hearts would u[F#m]p and melt away
[D]From the s[Amaj7]now in the nighttim[E]e, just g[F#m]oing, and going
[D]and the s[Amaj7]tirrin' of windchime[E]s, in the m[F#m]ornin', in the mornin'
