{comment: Verse 3}
[C#m]and Emi[F#]ly, I saw you last night by the river!
[C#m]I dre[F#]amed you were skippin' little stones across the surface of the water!
[G#m]Fro[B]wning at the a[A]ngle where they were l[C#m]ost and slipped under forever
[G#m]In a mud[B]-cloud, mica-s[A]pangled, like the sk[C#m]y'd been breathing on a mirror
[C#m]Any[F#]how -- I sat by your side, by the water
[C#m]You tau[F#]ght me the names of the stars overhead that I wrote down in my ledger
[G#m]Though all[B] I knew of the r[A]ote universe were those P[C#m]leiades loosed in December
[G#m]I pro[B]mised you I'd s[A]et them to verse so I[C#m]'d always remember

{comment: Chorus}
[C#m]That the met[F#]eorite is a source of the light, and the meteor's just what we see
[G#m]and the met[B]eoroid is a s[A]tone that's devoid of the f[C#m]ire that propelled it to thee
[C#m]and the met[F#]eorite's just what causes the light and the meteor's how it's perceived
[G#m]and the met[B]eoroid's a bone t[A]hrown from the void that lies q[C#m]uiet and offering to thee

