{comment: Verse 6}
[C#m]and say[F#], say, say, in the lee of the bay, don't be bothered!
[C#m]Leave your tro[F#]ubles here where the tugboats shear the water from the water
[G#m]Fla[B]nked by furrows, c[A]urling back like a m[C#m]atch held up to the newspaper

[C#m]Emi[F#]ly, they'll follow your lead by the letter!
[C#m]and I mak[F#]e this claim, and I'm not ashamed to say I knew you better!
[G#m]For wha[B]t they've seen is j[A]ust a beam of your s[C#m]un that banishes winter

[C#m]Let[F#] us go! Though we know it's a hopeless endeavor,
[C#m]The tie[F#]s that bind; they are barbed and spined and hold us close forever!
[G#m]Though the[B]re is nothing would help m[A]e come to grips with a s[C#m]ky that is gaping and yawning
