{comment: Verse 7}
[C]C[Em]ome on home, the po[D]ppies are all g[Am]rown knee-deep by now
[C]B[Em]lossoms all have fa[D]llen, and the p[Am]ollen ruins the plow
[C]P[Em]eonies nod in[D] the breeze, and w[Am]hile they wetly bow
[C]With h[Em]ydrocephali[D]tic listlessn[Am]ess, ants mop up their brows
[C]and e[Em]verything with wi[D]ngs is restless, a[Am]imless, drunk and dour
[C]B[Em]utterflies and bi[D]rds collide at h[Am]ot, ungodly hours
[C]and m[Em]y clay-coloured mo[D]therlessness r[Am]angily reclines
[C]C[Em]ome on home, now! Al[D]l my bones are d[Am]olorous with vines!

{comment: Verse 8}
[F]P[A]a pointed o[E]ut to me, for the h[F#m]undredth time tonight
[F]T[A]he way the L[E]adle leads to a d[F#m]irt-red bullet of light
[D]Squint s[A]kyward and l[E]isten, loving h[F#m]im, we move within his borders
[D]J[A]ust aster[E]isms in the s[F#m]tars set order
[D]We could s[A]tand for a century, [E]staring [F#m]with our heads cocked
[D]In the broad d[A]aylight at this thin[E]g -- J[F#m]oy! Landlocked!
[D]In b[A]odies that d[E]on't keep, d[F#m]umbstruck with the sweetness of being!
[D]'til w[A]e don't b[E]e told, t[F#m]ake this, and eat this!

